"objects, events and concepts" is a distinction typical for many upper level ontologies (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upper_ontology): DOLCE, BUFO, PROTON. The baseline is that objects exist (and have spatial and temporal extent), happenings happen (they have spatial extent; with two sub-classes: dynamic events and internally static situations) and there are also abstract concept, which don't have spatial and temporal extent (the number Pi, for instance).
